sentences: Timothy L. Aymar (born September 4, 1963) is an American heavy metal singer.
Often known for his strong vocals on Chuck Schuldiner's Control Denied band  but his music career as a vocalist started years before that.
He's been a vocalist since 1985 with 313 band, then he joined Triple x and released an album with them.

Aymar's band Triple-X won the In Pittsburgh Music Awards for Best Metal Band in 1990, and was the first regional band to be awarded a national sponsorship, which was from Anheuser-Busch/Budweiser Anheuser-Busch.
Tim was also voted 'Vocalist of the Year' in readers polls of many of the Pittsburgh Tri-State Area's rock and entertainment publications.
